Seeing you all in Toronto was such a joy! 💖💖 We hope that everyone had a good time at SHEIN's first-ever POP UP in Canada. We definitely will be back! 👏🏻

We have preserved these memories in pictures and films and we look forward to seeing you at our upcoming pop-up events!

THERE WERE LITTLE KNOWN FACTS ABOUT THE SHEIN TORONTO POP UP! DID YOU NOTICE THEM DURING YOUR VISIT?

1⃣. Molo wall and seating: The award-winning wall was displaying our evoluSHEIN logo and the soft stools you sat on to take photos inside the flower garden were part of an award-winning collection from Stephanie Forsythe and Todd MacAllen at molo design in Vancouver. Made from paper and textile the wall and seating elements are durable, reusable, and endlessly adaptable. Want a closer look? See them at our next pop-up!
 
2⃣. Our plantable wildflower seed postcard: A few lucky children were given an adorable postcard by SHEIN that was embedded with wildflower seeds to plant and grow.  The paper composts when soil and water is added and the seeds emerge. Share your experience growing these flowers using @shein_ca and tag #sheinthe6ixblossoms. Grow new memories and receive a pre-registered ticket to our next pop-up!
 
3⃣. All the products from our SHEIN Toronto pop-up were donated to national not-for-profit @newcirclesto. This grass-roots agency builds strong and caring communities by providing much-needed clothing, employment skills training, and settlement support to individuals living in poverty.
